#
# The following packages explicitly state the version of the linux kernel to
# be installed, as well as any packages that are kernel specific (e.g. tools
# like perf, that are tied to the kernel version). Any additional tools that
# are not specific to the kernel version should be included in the list
# below.
#
 * linux-generic
 * linux-tools-generic

#
# The following packages are tools that are intended for human convenience.
# These should not be relied on them programmatically. They may be updated
# or replaced without regard for backward compatibility.
#
 * atop
 * bpfcc-tools
 * dnsutils
 * dstat
 * emacs
 * gdb
 * glances
 * iftop
 * inotify-tools
 * procinfo
 * sg3-utils
 * strace
 * tshark
 * vim
